{"$ambrosia":"aero:interactive:9417ac60-5f60-11ea-8e69-affb2224d7e8:*","$id":"10fcf610-44e0-11ed-850f-b335f2ac1af4","$workspaceId":"7fff47c0-44d6-11ed-bcef-d5307f42495c","$projectId":"86cb0040-44df-11ed-8442-dbcbc27803ca","annotations":[],"configSchemaVersion":"/pluginGenericSchema/v1","config":{"stage":{"sections":[{"rowsAreFullWidth":false,"backgroundImageUrl":"","rows":[{"columns":[{"stageElements":[{"type":"stage-element-text","value":{"object":"value","document":{"object":"document","data":{},"nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"heading-two","ref":"930718e1-63d7-4e1f-836f-623f674c7b09","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Economies of Scale and Scope","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]}},"config":{"cssClass":""},"ref":"b472a720-0540-434b-97c4-e9325b84007c"}]}]},{"columns":[{"stageElements":[{"type":"stage-element-text","value":{"object":"value","document":{"object":"document","data":{},"nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"8c2eeb11-1d08-414e-a6fd-96a3c373631a","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"A large company can enjoy ","marks":[]},{"data":{"ref":"788b27ee-783b-43fb-b9db-4dfa97bce324","stage":{"ref":"6403f44e-24c1-446a-8973-fed23dae9be3","sections":[{"ref":"a71d02f6-1060-4097-be32-a33a65a9a031","rows":[{"ref":"481b6a2d-f27c-4d3b-bb34-712dc7e39508","columns":[{"ref":"3bcb5f7e-c00e-4cf2-aa4b-6efe6c8bffcb","stageElements":[{"ref":"7699825b-27b9-493e-9bac-5a5d85e73f30","type":"stage-element-text","value":{"object":"value","document":{"object":"document","data":{},"nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"button","ref":"f54b85fa-b7ba-4b15-a808-a4531d24545e","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"2751b651-fe8a-4b37-b392-dba13ed29ec1","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"The savings a large company can enjoy from producing goods in high volume, that are not available to a small company.","marks":[]}],"data":{}}],"data":{}}]}}}]}]}]}]}},"nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"economies of scale","marks":[{"type":"bold"}]}],"object":"inline","type":"key-term","ref":"f57d7b1a-1223-4da2-a4df-c04fb2d5cbb9"},{"object":"text","text":", or savings from producing goods in high volume, that are not available to a small company. For example, in Stride Rite’s acquisition of sports shoemaker Saucony in 2005, one motivation was to reduce Saucony’s manufacturing costs because, due to its larger size, Stride Rite could negotiate superior manufacturing contracts in China. Larger firms can also benefit from ","marks":[]},{"data":{"ref":"a156be24-5129-4967-9c47-41d279d448de","stage":{"ref":"16f1ed1a-b331-4818-9002-d6fe9baa89d7","sections":[{"ref":"b0e186c6-33e7-4ace-89f2-06fd0b83f55a","rows":[{"ref":"fca507fc-22fe-40a3-a446-f675b8ba8d65","columns":[{"ref":"6e1772c8-4a4e-4cb4-b67b-fa1bd17fe005","stageElements":[{"ref":"bbaaa0de-59f9-402e-a9a9-07a7ca5719a0","type":"stage-element-text","value":{"object":"value","document":{"object":"document","data":{},"nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"button","ref":"a708de90-f9b8-44f6-bf3d-c4259ec992b9","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"f720eead-c519-4ad2-98da-66cf73ccac9c","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Savings large companies can realize that come from combining the marketing and distribution of different types of related products.","marks":[]}],"data":{}}],"data":{}}]}}}]}]}]}]}},"nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"economies of scope","marks":[{"type":"bold"}]}],"object":"inline","type":"key-term","ref":"39c5fe41-ee54-493b-acdb-3eb29ceb7322"},{"object":"text","text":", which are savings that come from combining the marketing and distribution of different types of related products (e.g., soft drinks and snack foods).","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]}},"config":{"cssClass":""},"ref":"670996d5-2127-4eaf-9230-dba43f093347"}]}]},{"columns":[{"stageElements":[{"type":"stage-element-text","value":{"object":"value","document":{"object":"document","data":{},"nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"6a9bcedb-7d81-4ec8-8feb-ab1b7f0a6315","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"There may also be costs associated with size. Chief among these is that larger firms are more difficult to manage. In a small firm, the CEO is often close to the firm’s operations. She can keep in touch with the firm’s largest customers and most important personnel, thereby keeping abreast of changing market conditions and potential problems. Because they receive information quickly, managers of small firms are often able to react in a timely way to changes in the economic environment.","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]}},"config":{"cssClass":""},"ref":"02eb7141-d5b8-47d2-a45d-c2bdb31b21b8"}]}]}]}]},"screenType":"","transitions":{"enter":{"animation":"","duration":0,"easing":"","customKeyframes":""},"exit":{"animation":"","duration":0,"easing":"","customKeyframes":""}},"lockElements":false,"learnerCurrentAttempt":1,"footer":{"buttonText":"Next","buttonIcon":"Arrow","showFooter":false,"showHistoryNavButtons":false,"previewFooter":false,"position":"Fixed to screen bottom","footerComponent":{"showFooterDropArea":"hide","width":100,"footerComponentsAlignment":"right"}},"styles":{"background":{},"stage":{"maxWidth":940,"background":"rgba(255, 255, 255, 1)","responsive":true,"padding":{"vertical":60,"horizontal":60},"border":{"color":"rgba(224, 224, 224, 1)","radius":0,"width":0}},"elements":{"padding":{"vertical":10,"horizontal":10}},"footer":{"buttonColor":"rgba(0, 115, 202, 1)","textColor":"rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.7)","backgroundColor":"rgba(255, 255, 255, 1)","padding":10,"corners":4,"border":"none","shadow":"0 -1px 4px 0 rgba(0,0,0,0.06), 0 0 12px 2px rgba(0,0,0,0.1)"},"feedback":{"width":320,"textColor":"rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.7)","backgroundColor":"rgba(255, 255, 255, 1)","corners":4,"border":"none","shadow":"0 5px 47px 10px rgba(0,0,0,0.15), 0 10px 20px 2px rgba(0,0,0,0.1), 0 7px 8px 0 rgba(0,0,0,0.1)"}},"title":"Economies of Scale and Scope"},"assets":[],"scenarios":[],"pluginPayload":{"pluginRepositoryPath":"https://plugin-repository-bronte-qaint.pearson.com/9417ac60-5f60-11ea-8e69-affb2224d7e8/0.15.209/ac43ee4c0e